content.description: Start with hands on crimps, and walk onto the bottom of the boulder. Find your way up the face on tiny holds. Once you reach the top, traverse right, and downclimb the shallow, right-facing corner. This is a fun warm-up for the area.
content.location: This is located on the left end of the large, flat face bove where your right hand would be for the start of The Compactor.

content.description: Sit start on the jug, and top out up and a little left.
content.location: Around the back side of the boulder, you’ll see the jug after the two aretes.

content.description: Sit start matched on diagonal rail at 3-4 feet. Work your way up to the big shelf, then move left a bit to finish up on Trash Day.
content.location: This is on the left side of the boulder if looking at it from the power lines.

content.description: Sit start the right arete to its peak.
content.location: It is on the backside from the compactor.

content.description: From a sit, climb the left arete up to the peak.
content.location: This is on the back side from the compactor.

content.description: Start sitting with one hand on each arête, and compress your way to the top.
content.protection: At least 2 pads and some spotters.
content.location: This is visible from the trail (to the right).

content.description: Climb from the sitting position with a nice ringlock right hand over your left hand which is a thumb up jam. Work up the crack using foot hold to the left when there is a rock to your left, then foot jam until you can top out.
content.protection: A pad and a good spot the crux is the last move before pulling you feet out of the last possible foot jam.
content.location: Ascend the obvious crack up the left side of the Trash Can Boulder.

content.description: This is the first boulder on the right. Core, core, core.
